        <updateDate>2017-08-28T20:18:44Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Reaffirming DHS Commitment to Countering All Forms of Extremism</strong></p> <p>This bill prohibits the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) from changing the name of its Countering Violent Extremism Task Force.</p> <p>DHS may not make grants to counter Islamist extremism in an aggregate amount of more than $4 million in any fiscal year and shall ensure that any such grants made for a fiscal year are closely matched in aggregate dollar amounts in grants made to counter other forms of extremism for such fiscal year. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
